The decision of the FAA applies to the American airline companies.
However, we are always interested by the lawful evolutions which could profit with the passengers, and we will examine closely the decision of the FAA and the reasons of this one.
For the American carriers, the impact of the decision will vary from one airline company to another and will depend on the age of their fleet.
The carriers will have to show that theirs planes can tolerate radio operator interferences coming from electronic devices, just as to re-examine the handbooks, the equipment of formation, the programme of transport of hand luggage and the instructions provided to the passengers.
“As soon as an airline company checked the tolerance of its fleet, it can authorize the passengers to use light portable electronic devices, like shelves, readers of e-books and smartphones at all the altitudes”, the FAA declared.
